<br>
<br>
Warriors are a dime a dozen. Melees in general are, as they're nowhere near as hard to master as the caster classes. This isn't open to debate, it's simple fact. The well played warrior is at the top of a mob's aggro list when they're tanking, and they basically have to stop using taunt to stay off the top of the aggro list when they're not. (Or switch to slower weapons, which often means doing more damage.)<br>
<br>
The well played wizard is always at the 2nd spot on the mob's aggro list. If they're doing their job, they die 2nd, right after the tank. Having played both, I can say it's an awful lot harder to stay at number 2 than it is to stay at number 1. Very few actually master the intricacies, and either end up dying frequently, or sitting down until the mob reaches 40% hitpoints and then starting to nuke, which is basically useless in most cases.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Warriors are very common, but because of misconceptions about the strengths of various classes, the warrior has a much easier time finding a group than the Wizard. You'll find yourself doing a lot of soloing or guild grouping once you pass 30 or so, and having read idiotic posts like those in that &quot;what's the worst class&quot; thread, I don't see that problem fixing itself soon. It's a double edged sword, however. If the warrior is poorly played, doesn't use his discs when needed, doesn't taunt, or whatever, they're also very easy to replace.<br>
<br>
<br>
Then comes the high end game. This is where the wizard will shine the most: aside from velk's gimps, the majority of high end grouping is done in an area where a wizard or druid is absolutely a must-have: without them, you can't evacuate, and often can't even get there to begin with.<br>
<br>
And then there's raid encounters. It has been recorded on more than one occasion where a solo wizard has outdamaged an entire raid force and stolen experience on dragon-level kills. The 55+ (possibly the 51+, in some cases) wizard completely owns the raid scene. Here, we are in our element, doing exactly what we were designed to do: deal huge amounts of damage in a short amount of time. My personal record so far is just shy of 20,000 damage in less than 1 minute, and I was level 55 at the time (was lucky, no resists). It may not seem like much when you consider ubermobs like Ventani, or other million+ hitpoints mobs, but consider that 20,000 is more than half of Lady Vox's hitpoints, and 1/5th-1/10th the hitpoints of most of the raid encounters in Velious outside of Sleeper's and NToV. This is probably why 55+, and especially 60 wizards are among the 3 most sought-after classes in high end guilds.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
What it all boils down to, however, is what you want to play. Personally, I'd say wizard all the way. I love the wizard class, and I love what we're capable of. It may not be the right choice for you, however. You may find that the trouble finding a group pre-50 is just too much, and give up. There's no shame in that, as I'd estimate that more than half of wizards give up before they reach 50+. It can be far more rewarding, and far more gratifying, though, to know that you're good at what you do, and that really <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> good</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> members of your clase are rare.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
